48. At laudat, &c., an objection of the Stoics, to which Et quidem (“ quite right, exactly so ”) is Cicero’s ironical reply. The sense of what follows is this: Since Epicurus holds that the supreme good consists in pleasure ; virtue is not his supreme good, and therefore his encomiums of it are an inconsequence.
